<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Helper classes for Zend_Gdata_HttpClient (such as Zend_Gdata_ClientLogin) offer constructor parameters to set an application's useragent for use when making requests. However, there is no easy way to set this without using a constructor parameter, and no such parameter exists for Zend_Gdata_HttpClient.</p>

<p>Instead, users must build a config array and call setConfig(). This is non-obvious, and results in a low number of applications setting their useragent.</p>

<p>Zend_Gdata_HttpClinet should offer a (possibly mandatory) useragent setter.</p>

